sentences: (Urdu: حبِیب ولی محمد‎), (16 January 1921 –  3 September 2014) was a Pakistani ghazal and film playback singer.
Habib Wali Mohammad was born on January 16, 1921 at Rangoon to a conservative Memon family, which later moved to Mumbai.
He received his MBA from Syracuse University, New York in 1947, and then lived in Mumbai for about 10 years before moving to Pakistan.
